This Snapshot Released On Saturday April 4 2026

1 Added Support Plasma Login Manager

For Existing Triaxis User

Go To tty3 Then sudo systemctl stop sddm sudo systemctl disable sddm then sudo pacman -R sddm then sudo pacman -S plasma-login-manager Then sudo systemctl enable plasmalogin Then sudo systemctl start plasmalogin
Then Login To KDE Plasma Using PLM Then Open System Settings Then Security & Privacy Then Login Screen Then Configure Appearance Then Select Frozenworld Or Frozenworld Compile it
Then Go To Screen Locking Then Configure Appearance Then Select Frozenworld Or Frozenworld Compile it

2 Added Splash on systemd boot which affected to Triaxis GNU/Linux Even Though Triaxis Uses GRUB Not systemd-boot
  To To Do This Run sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/systemd/bootctl/splash-arch.bmp
  Then sudo nano /usr/share/systemd/bootctl/arch.conf Change title  Arch Linux To title   Triaxis GNU/Linux
  Then sudo mkinitcpio -P
